      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nJames, reran with Test-Parameters: trivial=true testlist=sanity-benchmark. However, pios_ssf is getting skipped.\n\nThe message is coming from  test_pios_ssf where -z test fails. “SKIP: sanity-benchmark test_pios_ssf /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity-benchmark.sh : pios not found PIOSBIN=“. And this is coming when PIOSBIN is not getting assigned by this statement PIOSBIN=${PIOSBIN:-$(which pios 2> /dev/null || true)}.\n\nCould you please check here, or there is something I can do?\n\nThanks",
